      <h2>Editorial Illustration for Penn Appétit Magazine Fall 2014</h2>

      <div class="description" style="width:380px; padding-right:20px">
        <p> Penn Appétit is an innovative, student-run food magazine at the University of Pennsylvania which showcases the best eats in Philly and beyond. <br>[<a href="http://pennappetit.com/">Website Link</a>]</p>

        <p>Penn Appétit publishes one hard copy issue each semester, and collaborates with the Digital Illustration course at Penn. Students are supplied with a list of article (usually narrowed down to three), and each chooses one to create an 8.5" x 11" conceptual illustration for. Penn Appétit then picks one illustration per article that will be featured in the magazine.</p>

        <p>I chose the article <i>Cooking with Wood: Building the Right Smoke</i>, which elaborated on the different aromata of each wood as well as what food they should be used with. Obvious keywords here are "wood", "smoke", and perhaps "smoked meat".</p>

